 important to get ahead in the game than it is to try and be apart of something you helped to create?<br><br>I digress.<br><br>I don't feel upset about it, but I guess I do feel disappointed.  I wonder what this game would be like if no one had any loyalty.  How many more people should the loyal person help before they realize that they are wasting their time?<br> <p><TABLE ALIGN="LEFT"><TR><TD WIDTH=150 ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT COLOR="#009900">Manas Pineblade:</font></TD><TD WIDTH=150 ALIGN="LEFT">44 Ranger (ACTIVE)</TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH=150 ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT COLOR="#800080">Nural:</font></TD><TD WIDTH=150 ALIGN="LEFT">51 Vicar(ACTIVE)</TD></TR><tr><td><image src="http://www.angelfire.com/ego/psicopro/as.gif"><tr><td><a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/bmanaseq">Guild Leader</a></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umystykal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mystykal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Never Asks Nicely :)</span><br>  Posts: 671<br> <font color=#333333>(10/6/01 10:50:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Serious discussion (can that happen here?)</span><hr size=1> I can give some input on this Manas.<br><br>There are different kinds of guilds in this game.  <br><br>1-There are the guilds created for a small group of friends....I've seen these don't usually last that long.  Sometimes just something to get you going when you and your friends first start playing.<br><br>2-There are &quot;casual&quot; guilds.  I find these guilds to have the majority of the people not leveling past level 50.  They pride themselves on their &quot;family&quot; atmosphere and how much everyone loves each other.  Most of these people have no desire to let this game take over all of their personal time, they don't have HUGE goals in this game, they come to the came to hang out and talk to their friends and to have fun without having to put in a lot of hard work.<br><br>3-There are the &quot;uber&quot; guilds.  These people consist mostly of power gamers who play a LOT of hours and wanna kill the biggest baddest shit in the game.<br><br>Sometimes when people start to play they start off casually joining either type 1 or type 2 guilds.  Even though they love the people in their guild, their goals change and they want to kill the big bad shit, their goals are no longer the same of their guilds goals, so they move on.  This doesn't mean they don't like you, this means they want something different.  It doesn't mean they &quot;used&quot; you to get shit and then &quot;abandoned&quot; you.  <br><br>Yes, there are people that jump from guild to guild looking for who knows what.  I'm not talking about these people, I'm talking about the &quot;majority&quot; of people. (I think)<br><br>Let me tell you about my guild experience.  When I first started playing, I started playing with a large group of RL friends.  There were about 15 of us.  We all played at different times mostly and didn't play a lot of hours.  We formed our little guild so we wouldn't fill up each others friends lists but could see when we were on.  There were usually not more than 2 or 3 people on at once unless we had it scheduled, and on those times half of us were in one house, the other half were on a conference call with us.  This of course didn't last too long as some of us still only played a couple hours a week, and others played 30+ hours a week.<br><br>I then moved on to Knights of Phoenix.  While in KoP, I began to play more and more, leveling myself up.  But then the more I played and the higher I got, the more I wanted out of the game.  KoP  was not doing the high level game that I wanted to do, so I joined Crusaders of Plilo.  <br><br>COP will be my last guild I am in.  I don't play the game much anymore, but when I do, they are doing the things I want to do.  This has nothing to do with items or equipment, this has more to do with the level of game I choose to play.<br><br>This is my long winded post of the year, I hope this gives some insight into what you were looking for, if not, sorry for the wasted space. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Honestly though Manas, I don't think there should be so much hurt feelings when someone decides the guild they are in is not for them anymore. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><strong><b><BR>Mystykal Forse<BR>Cleric Of Zeb<BR>Crusaders of Plilo</b></strong><BR><end><end></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uscytheeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ScytheEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(10/6/01 12:59:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Serious discussion (can that happen here?)</span><hr size=1> &quot;to have fun without having to put in a lot of hard work&quot;<br><br>A common misconception <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Many smaller guilds just don't consider raids to be rewarding.  Boring/tedious != hard work.  Many players are just not willing to live with a ratio of 95% preparation/recovery time and 5% actual action.<br><br> <p></p><i></i>